# CMe — Git Branching & File Scoping Rules

## Branching Strategy

This project uses **trunk-based development with short-lived feature branches**.

- `main` is the stable trunk. It is always deployable.
- Feature work happens on branches named `feat/<screen>-<feature>` (e.g. `feat/applicant-intake-sections`, `feat/employer-weighting-ui`).
- Each branch targets **one** screen or **one** cross-cutting concern. Never mix applicant and employer work on the same branch.
- Merge back to `main` when complete. Delete the branch after merge.

### Branch naming

```
feat/applicant-<feature>      → Applicant view work
feat/employer-<feature>       → Employer view work
feat/shared-<feature>         → Shared components, contexts, types, auth
feat/assessment-<feature>     → Assessment link / cold-start flow
feat/pulsecheck-<feature>     → Post-hire pulse check flow
fix/<description>             → Bug fixes
chore/<description>           → Tooling, config, migrations
```

## Before starting any task

1. Confirm which screen the task belongs to (applicant / employer / assessment / pulsecheck / shared).
2. Check you are on the correct feature branch — if not, create or switch to one.
3. List the files you expect to modify.
4. If any file is outside that screen’s scope (see below), explain why before touching it.
5. Proceed only after scoping is clear.

## File scoping

Only modify files within the current screen’s scope. Touching shared files requires explicit justification.

### Applicant View

```
src/components/ApplicantScreen.tsx
src/components/applicant-pages/**
```

### Employer View

```
src/components/EmployerScreen.tsx
src/components/employer-pages/**
```

### Assessment Link

```
src/pages/AssessmentLink.tsx
```

### Pulse Check

```
src/pages/PulseCheckForm.tsx
```

### Shared (high-risk — justify before changing)

```
src/App.tsx
src/contexts/**
src/lib/**
src/types/**
src/styles/**
supabase/**
```

## Hard rules

- **Never** modify `App.tsx` navigation unless the task explicitly requires a new route or tab.
- **Never** modify another screen’s components while working on a different screen’s feature.
- **Never** change `UserProfileContext.tsx`, `supabaseClient.ts`, `authRouting.ts`, or type files without stating exactly what will change and why.
- **Always** show the specific line you plan to change before making any change to an existing file (pre-confirmation step).
- Keep shared file changes minimal and backwards-compatible.
